<n-docbody><doc bill="Y"><content.metadata.block><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.second.line.cite><bop/><bos/>Multidistrict Lit Man § 4:2<eos/><eop/></cmd.second.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block><prop.block><prop.head toc-guid=""><bop/><bos/><headtext>Multidistrict Litigation Manual</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><content.metadata.block><cmd.dates><cmd.currency.default iso.d="20190501"><bop/><bos/>May 2019 Update<eos/><eop/></cmd.currency.default></cmd.dates></content.metadata.block><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>David F. Herr[<footnote.reference refid="If25016316b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">a0</footnote.reference>]</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><prop.head toc-guid="I97b7f560933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Part</label.name><label.designator>I.</label.designator><headtext>Handling Cases Before the Judicial Panel on Multidistrict Litigation</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><prop.head toc-guid="Ib978dbb0933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Chapter</label.name><label.designator>4.</label.designator><headtext>Procedure Before the Panel</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head></prop.block><message.block><include.copyright n-include_collection="w_wlnv_msg" n-include_guid="I1DA35ED81DD211B281BAD200220BDFCA">Copyright (c) 2017 Thomson/RIA All rights reserved.</include.copyright></message.block><section><section.front><doc.title toc-guid="I94edf721e1e311da9c26e67ca3b71335"><head parent="doc.title"><bop/><bos/><label.name>§ </label.name><label.designator>4:2.</label.designator><headtext>Right to appear before the Panel</headtext><eos/><eop/></head></doc.title></section.front><section.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>The right to appear before the Panel is extended to all lawyers who are admitted to practice in any of the federal district courts.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If2503d406b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">1</footnote.reference>] This right to appear is qualified in one important way–it is extended only to those who maintain a CM/ECF account in any federal court. <eos/><bos/>It is not necessary for lawyers in transferor court actions to apply for <ital>pro hac vice</ital> admission to practice before the Panel and there is no separate “bar” of the Panel.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>The Panel rules also extend to all lawyers in transferred actions the right to continue to appear in the transferee courts, without applying for admission and without requiring retention of local counsel.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If25175c06b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">2</footnote.reference>]</paratext><eos/><eop/></para></section.body></section><author.footnotes><footnote ID="If25016316b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>a0</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>Maslon Edelman Borman &amp; Brand, LLP, Minneapolis, Minnesota.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></author.footnotes><footnote.block><footnote ID="If2503d406b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>1</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>J.P.M.L. <eos/><bos/><cite.query w-src-number="0304913969" w-seq-number="00001" w-ref-type="LQ" w-normalized-cite="USMULTIDISTLITR2.1" w-pub-number="1000604" ID="I5373c0706b3e11e9a5a983883834314b">R. 2.1(c)</cite.query>. <eos/><bos/>The rules are reproduced in <cite.query w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs4:34" w-pub-number="185218" ID="If2503d416b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">§ 4:34</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If25175c06b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>2</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>Id.<eos/></ital></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></footnote.block><content.metadata.block><cmd.royalty><cmd.copyright><bop/><bos/>Westlaw. © 2019 Thomson Reuters.  <eos/><bos/>No Claim to Orig. U.S. Govt. <eos/><bos/>Works.<eos/><eop/></cmd.copyright></cmd.royalty><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.first.line.cite><bop/><bos/>MDLITMAN § 4:2<eos/><eop/></cmd.first.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block></doc></n-docbody>
